# database/ — PostgreSQL Initialization

## Purpose
Contains init.sql which PostgreSQL runs automatically on first container start
(mounted at /docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/ in docker-compose.yml).

## Tables (init.sql)
- users             — id, email, password, name, role (ENUM: BUYER/SELLER/ADMIN), created_at
- stores            — id, user_id (FK→users), name, logo, description
- categories        — id, name
- category_items    — product_id + category_id (many-to-many join)
- products          — id, store_id, name, price, stock, images, description
- cart_items        — id, user_id, product_id, quantity
- orders            — id, buyer_id, status ENUM (waiting_approval/approved/rejected/on_delivery/received)
- order_items       — id, order_id, product_id, quantity, price
- reviews           — id, order_item_id, user_id, rating, comment
- review_responses  — seller response to a review
- review_images     — image paths attached to reviews
- auctions          — id, product_id, seller_id, start_price, current_price, end_time, status
- auction_bids      — id, auction_id, bidder_id, amount, created_at
- chat_rooms        — id, buyer_id, seller_id
- chat_messages     — id, room_id, sender_id, content, created_at
- push_subscriptions — Web Push VAPID subscription objects per user

## Notes
- Only runs on fresh volume. To re-init: `docker compose down -v && docker compose up`
- Timezone: Asia/Jakarta (set in postgres command and TZ env var)
- No migrations system — schema changes require manual ALTER or full reinit
